# 1. Create a Minimal Package

A minimal PHP package, that can be installed using `composer`, can include just a single `composer.json` file.

We already know we'll definitely need several packages, so add those in `require` and `require` dev sections.
```
{
    "name": "good-system/core",
    "require": {
        "laravel/framework": "5.7.*",
        "good-system/laravel-o365auth": "*",
        "braintree/braintree_php": "^3.38.0"
    },
    "require-dev": {
        "beyondcode/laravel-dump-server": "^1.0",
        "filp/whoops": "^2.0",
        "fzaninotto/faker": "^1.4",
        "mockery/mockery": "^1.0",
        "nunomaduro/collision": "^2.0",
        "phpunit/phpunit": "^7.0"
    },
    "minimum-stability": "dev",
    "autoload": {
        "psr-4": {
            "GoodSystem\\": "src"
        }
    }
}
```
